2017-05-02$17:21:55.618Z$z130s5kqjkzygttnl23qd3dbzoeuxjh2d$Found this new paper: From n-qubit multi-particle quantum teleportation modelling to n-qudit contextuality...$N$https://plus.google.com/116520526147217731163/posts/L322uxdtt5N$post$Gupta Akshintala$116520526147217731163$https://plus.google.com/116520526147217731163$$$$'Found this new paper: From n-qubit multi-particle quantum teleportation modelling to n-qudit contextuality based quantum teleportation and beyond

Abstract
This paper further generalizes the modelling framework for contextuality based quantum teleportation to n-dimensional quantum states
column2: or n-qudits (quantum odd-prime based units) which holds considerable promise for even higher mathematical abstraction. The proposed generalization extends the two states in the qubit model
column3: to n states and this n could tend towards infinity. We are heading towards point-sized loops or fine-grained particles of nature
column4: which have been rejected out of hand by string theorists. It is not physical reality when measured from the sense of Planck\\u2019s length of 10\\u221235 metres
column5: but finer-grained particles than Planck\\u2019s length 10\\u221235 metres may exist
column7: they are not matter anymore. We argue that why stop at degree of freedom of three
